<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1922-11-23T02:34:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1922-11-23T02:34:00-05:00" n="773" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d773">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">861.77/2850: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Former President of the Technical Board</hi>
                                (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Stevens</hi></persName>)
                                <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Harbin</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-11-23T16:00:00+08:26"><hi rend="italic">November 23,
                                        1922—4 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received 4:47
                            p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>I am leaving to-day for Peking on first lap of going to the United
                            States. Secretary of Technical Board will remain short time to close up
                            details. Any instructions should be sent to Harbin in my name which if
                            necessary will reach me Peking through the secretary who retains
                            code.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Stevens</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>